The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 June is 42,256 (4,890.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 May, there were 78 new confirmed cases (9.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 May, there were 44 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 77% (34 extra cases).
